# Fleet Crew & Officer Canon

**Canonical source:** `Universe/Fleet/fleet_crew_and_officer_canon.md`

Reference before scenes aboard Fleet vessels. Systems rules — not narrative content. **Overrides all previous crew size values.**

## Crew complements (canon)

| Class | Crew |
|-------|------|
| Scout | 20 |
| Corvette | 40 |
| Destroyer | 80 |
| Frigate | 150 |
| Cruiser | 300 |
| Heavy Cruiser | 600 |
| Battleship | 2,000 |
| Fleet Carrier | 3,000 (400 fighters) |
| Dreadnaught | 8,000 |
| Titan | 25,000 |
| Leviathan | 60,000 |

## Design goal

Ships = military ecosystems, **not** cities. Even Leviathans are fleet-defining warships with controlled complements — not population-scale habitats.

## Officer scaling

- **Scout–Frigate:** small centralized command; officers know most crew
- **Cruiser–HC:** multi-team departments; focus on department heads
- **Battleship+:** structured hierarchy; narrative follows bridge/CIC/key departments only
- **Dreadnaught–Leviathan:** multi-department command; comprehensible by narrative focus — boarding targets sections

## Kestrel Veil (Book One)

Fleet standard: **20**. Narrative foregrounds **14** principal personnel — not the full complement.

